goal.en:
- Students have a preliminary understanding of Vietnam‘s cultural characteristics, such as major cities, food, clothing, housing, and transportation in Vietnam;
- Learn the method of Vietnamese pinyin: 29 letters, tones, vowels, consonants, rhymes, and pronunciation of words;
- Learn Vietnamese appellations and how to use them when meeting and getting to know each other;
- Learn Vietnamese numbers and apply them to ask time, date, quantity of items, shopping prices, etc.;
- Learn to introduce family members and self-introduction (nationality, age, occupation, interests, etc.);
- Learn to use Vietnamese in general life situations, such as asking for directions, taking a ride, shopping, going to the market to buy ingredients, ordering food in restaurants, etc.
